{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":856,"text":"I want to introduce you\nto an amazing woman."},{"time":3690,"text":"Her name is Davinia."},{"time":6444,"text":"Davinia was born in Jamaica,\nemigrated to the US at the age of 18,"},{"time":10873,"text":"and now lives just outside\nof Washington, DC."},{"time":14262,"text":"She's not a high-powered\npolitical staffer,"},{"time":17088,"text":"nor a lobbyist."},{"time":18676,"text":"She'd probably tell you\nshe's quite unremarkable,"},{"time":21629,"text":"but she's having\nthe most remarkable impact."},{"time":24471,"text":"What's incredible about Davinia"},{"time":26015,"text":"is that she's willing to spend\ntime every single week"},{"time":28902,"text":"focused on people who are not her:"},{"time":31331,"text":"people not her in her neighborhood,\nher state, nor even in her country --"},{"time":35734,"text":"people she'd likely never meet."}]},{"cues":[{"time":37991,"text":"Davinia's impact started a few years ago"},{"time":39955,"text":"when she reached out\nto all of her friends on Facebook,"},{"time":42723,"text":"and asked them to donate their pennies"},{"time":44930,"text":"so she could fund girls' education."},{"time":47397,"text":"She wasn't expecting a huge response,"},{"time":49828,"text":"but 700,000 pennies later,"},{"time":52635,"text":"she's now sent over 120 girls to school."},{"time":55975,"text":"When we spoke last week,"},{"time":57186,"text":"she told me she's become\na little infamous at the local bank"},{"time":60248,"text":"every time she rocks up\nwith a shopping cart full of pennies."}]},{"cues":[{"time":65042,"text":"Now -- Davinia is not alone."},{"time":68161,"text":"Far from it."},{"time":69717,"text":"She's part of a growing movement."},{"time":72027,"text":"And there's a name\nfor people like Davinia:"},{"time":74663,"text":"global citizens."},{"time":76935,"text":"A global citizen is someone\nwho self-identifies first and foremost"},{"time":81430,"text":"not as a member of a state,\na tribe or a nation,"},{"time":85256,"text":"but as a member of the human race,"},{"time":87467,"text":"and someone who is prepared\nto act on that belief,"},{"time":92331,"text":"to tackle our world's greatest challenges."},{"time":95250,"text":"Our work is focused on finding,"},{"time":97727,"text":"supporting and activating global citizens."},{"time":100634,"text":"They exist in every country"},{"time":102556,"text":"and among every demographic."}]},{"cues":[{"time":105008,"text":"I want to make the case to you today"},{"time":106794,"text":"that the world's future depends\non global citizens."},{"time":109896,"text":"I'm convinced that if we had\nmore global citizens active in our world,"},{"time":114222,"text":"then every single one\nof the major challenges we face --"},{"time":116981,"text":"from poverty, climate change,\ngender inequality --"},{"time":120603,"text":"these issues become solvable."},{"time":122811,"text":"They are ultimately global issues,"},{"time":125431,"text":"and they can ultimately only be solved"},{"time":127336,"text":"by global citizens demanding\nglobal solutions from their leaders."}]},{"cues":[{"time":132731,"text":"Now, some people's immediate\nreaction to this idea"},{"time":135256,"text":"is that it's either a bit utopian\nor even threatening."},{"time":139561,"text":"So I'd like to share with you\na little of my story today,"},{"time":142640,"text":"how I ended up here,"},{"time":144375,"text":"how it connects with Davinia"},{"time":146187,"text":"and, hopefully, with you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":148256,"text":"Growing up in Melbourne, Australia,"},{"time":150096,"text":"I was one of those seriously\nirritating little kids"},{"time":153459,"text":"that never, ever stopped asking, \"Why?\""},{"time":155807,"text":"You might have been one yourself."},{"time":157426,"text":"I used to ask my mum\nthe most annoying questions."},{"time":160822,"text":"I'd ask her questions like,\n\"Mum, why I can't I dress up"},{"time":163645,"text":"and play with puppets all day?\""},{"time":165596,"text":"\"Why do you want fries with that?\""},{"time":167936,"text":"\"What is a shrimp,"},{"time":169150,"text":"and why do we have to keep\nthrowing them on the barbie?\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":171846,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":172871,"text":"\"And mum -- this haircut."},{"time":174703,"text":"Why?\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":175900,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":178126,"text":"The worst haircut, I think."},{"time":181364,"text":"Still terrible."}]},{"cues":[{"time":182539,"text":"As a \"why\" kid, I thought\nI could change the world,"},{"time":185365,"text":"and it was impossible\nto convince me otherwise."},{"time":187989,"text":"And when I was 12\nand in my first year of high school,"},{"time":190600,"text":"I started raising money\nfor communities in the developing world."},{"time":193861,"text":"We were a really\nenthusiastic group of kids,"},{"time":196080,"text":"and we raised more money\nthan any other school in Australia."},{"time":199365,"text":"And so I was awarded the chance\nto go to the Philippines to learn more."},{"time":202977,"text":"It was 1998."},{"time":204915,"text":"We were taken into a slum\nin the outskirts of Manila."},{"time":208626,"text":"It was there I became friends\nwith Sonny Boy,"},{"time":212380,"text":"who lived on what was literally\na pile of steaming garbage."},{"time":216617,"text":"\"Smoky Mountain\" was what they called it."},{"time":218650,"text":"But don't let the romance\nof that name fool you,"},{"time":220959,"text":"because it was nothing more\nthan a rancid landfill"},{"time":223344,"text":"that kids like Sonny Boy spent hours\nrummaging through every single day"},{"time":227709,"text":"to find something, anything of value."}]},{"cues":[{"time":231304,"text":"That night with Sonny Boy and his family\nchanged my life forever,"},{"time":234604,"text":"because when it came time to go to sleep,"},{"time":236651,"text":"we simply laid down on this concrete\nslab the size of half my bedroom"},{"time":240422,"text":"with myself, Sonny Boy,\nand the rest of his family,"},{"time":243352,"text":"seven of us in this long line,"},{"time":244987,"text":"with the smell of rubbish all around us"},{"time":247405,"text":"and cockroaches crawling all around."},{"time":249952,"text":"And I didn't sleep a wink,"},{"time":251255,"text":"but I lay awake thinking to myself,"},{"time":252988,"text":"\"Why should anyone have to live like this"},{"time":255494,"text":"when I have so much?"},{"time":257290,"text":"Why should Sonny Boy's ability\nto live out his dreams"},{"time":260060,"text":"be determined by where he's born,"},{"time":262130,"text":"or what Warren Buffett called\n'the ovarian lottery?'\""},{"time":265197,"text":"I just didn't get it,"},{"time":266978,"text":"and I needed to understand why."}]},{"cues":[{"time":269656,"text":"Now, I only later came to understand"},{"time":272026,"text":"that the poverty I'd seen\nin the Philippines"},{"time":274478,"text":"was the result of decisions made\nor not made, man-made,"},{"time":278811,"text":"by a succession of colonial powers\nand corrupt governments"},{"time":282240,"text":"who had anything but the interests\nof Sonny Boy at heart."},{"time":285429,"text":"Sure, they didn't create Smoky Mountain,\nbut they may as well have."},{"time":289253,"text":"And if we're to try to help\nkids like Sonny Boy,"},{"time":291878,"text":"it wouldn't work just to try\nto send him a few dollars"},{"time":294594,"text":"or to try to clean up\nthe garbage dump on which he lived,"},{"time":297706,"text":"because the core\nof the problem lay elsewhere."},{"time":300214,"text":"And as I worked on community\ndevelopment projects over the coming years"},{"time":303897,"text":"trying to help build schools,"},{"time":305763,"text":"train teachers, and tackle HIV and AIDS,"},{"time":308828,"text":"I came to see that community development"},{"time":311289,"text":"should be driven\nby communities themselves,"},{"time":313869,"text":"and that although charity is necessary,\nit's not sufficient."},{"time":317646,"text":"We need to confront these challenges"},{"time":319531,"text":"on a global scale and in a systemic way."},{"time":322221,"text":"And the best thing I could do"},{"time":323690,"text":"is try to mobilize a large group\nof citizens back home"},{"time":327221,"text":"to insist that our leaders engage\nin that systemic change."}]},{"cues":[{"time":331315,"text":"That's why, a few years later,"},{"time":333339,"text":"I joined with a group of college friends"},{"time":335632,"text":"in bringing the Make Poverty History\ncampaign to Australia."},{"time":339447,"text":"We had this dream of staging\nthis small concert"},{"time":342849,"text":"around the time of the G20\nwith local Aussie artists,"},{"time":346746,"text":"and it suddenly exploded one day"},{"time":348422,"text":"when we got a phone call from Bono,\nthe Edge and Pearl Jam,"},{"time":352048,"text":"who all agreed to headline our concert."},{"time":355341,"text":"I got a little bit excited\nthat day, as you can see."}]},{"cues":[{"time":357966,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":359928,"text":"But to our amazement,"},{"time":361231,"text":"the Australian government\nheard our collective voices,"},{"time":364347,"text":"and they agreed to double investment\ninto global health and development --"},{"time":368065,"text":"an additional 6.2 billion dollars."},{"time":371280,"text":"It felt like --"}]},{"cues":[{"time":372479,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":376962,"text":"It felt like this incredible validation."},{"time":379579,"text":"By rallying citizens together,\nwe helped persuade our government"},{"time":382969,"text":"to do the unthinkable,"},{"time":384479,"text":"and act to fix a problem\nmiles outside of our borders."}]},{"cues":[{"time":388965,"text":"But here's the thing:"},{"time":391156,"text":"it didn't last."},{"time":392999,"text":"See, there was a change in government,"},{"time":394919,"text":"and six years later, all that new money"},{"time":397631,"text":"disappeared."},{"time":399542,"text":"What did we learn?"},{"time":401703,"text":"We learned that one-off spikes\nare not enough."},{"time":405225,"text":"We needed a sustainable movement,"},{"time":407709,"text":"not one that is susceptible\nto the fluctuating moods of a politician"},{"time":411717,"text":"or the hint of an economic downturn."},{"time":414018,"text":"And it needed to happen everywhere;"},{"time":416144,"text":"otherwise, every individual government\nwould have this built-in excuse mechanism"},{"time":420073,"text":"that they couldn't possibly carry\nthe burden of global action alone."}]},{"cues":[{"time":425405,"text":"And so this is what we embarked upon."},{"time":428103,"text":"And as we embarked upon\nthis challenge, we asked ourselves,"},{"time":431104,"text":"how do we gain enough pressure\nand build a broad enough army"},{"time":434625,"text":"to win these fights for the long term?"},{"time":437419,"text":"We could only think of one way."},{"time":440034,"text":"We needed to somehow turn\nthat short-term excitement"},{"time":442769,"text":"of people involved with\nthe Make Poverty History campaign"},{"time":445690,"text":"into long-term passion."},{"time":447822,"text":"It had to be part of their identity."},{"time":450319,"text":"So in 2012, we cofounded an organization\nthat had exactly that as its goal."},{"time":455836,"text":"And there was only one name for it:"},{"time":458359,"text":"Global Citizen."}]},{"cues":[{"time":460241,"text":"But this is not about\nany one organization."},{"time":463295,"text":"This is about citizens taking action."},{"time":466041,"text":"And research data tells us"},{"time":467826,"text":"that of the total population\nwho even care about global issues,"},{"time":472081,"text":"only 18 percent have done\nanything about it."},{"time":476237,"text":"It's not that people don't want to act."},{"time":478595,"text":"It's often that they don't\nknow how to take action,"},{"time":481050,"text":"or that they believe that their actions\nwill have no effect."},{"time":484175,"text":"So we had to somehow recruit\nand activate millions of citizens"},{"time":487724,"text":"in dozens of countries"},{"time":489409,"text":"to put pressure on their leaders\nto behave altruistically."}]},{"cues":[{"time":492732,"text":"And as we did so, we discovered\nsomething really thrilling,"},{"time":496261,"text":"that when you make\nglobal citizenship your mission,"},{"time":499237,"text":"you suddenly find yourself\nwith some extraordinary allies."},{"time":502743,"text":"See, extreme poverty isn't the only issue\nthat's fundamentally global."},{"time":506632,"text":"So, too, is climate change,"},{"time":508520,"text":"human rights, gender equality,"},{"time":511120,"text":"even conflict."},{"time":512730,"text":"We found ourselves shoulder to shoulder"},{"time":515346,"text":"with people who are passionate about\ntargeting all these interrelated issues."}]},{"cues":[{"time":519316,"text":"But how did we actually\ngo about recruiting"},{"time":521377,"text":"and engaging those global citizens?"},{"time":523327,"text":"Well, we used the universal language:"},{"time":527034,"text":"music."},{"time":528287,"text":"We launched the Global Citizen Festival"},{"time":530574,"text":"in the heart of New York City\nin Central Park,"},{"time":533448,"text":"and we persuaded some of the world's\nbiggest artists to participate."},{"time":537240,"text":"We made sure that\nthese festivals coincided"},{"time":539580,"text":"with the UN General Assembly meeting,"},{"time":541745,"text":"so that leaders who need\nto hear our voices"},{"time":544223,"text":"couldn't possible ignore them."}]},{"cues":[{"time":546828,"text":"But there was a twist:"},{"time":548884,"text":"you couldn't buy a ticket."},{"time":550563,"text":"You had to earn it."},{"time":552220,"text":"You had to take action\non behalf of a global cause,"},{"time":555221,"text":"and only once you'd done that\ncould you earn enough points to qualify."},{"time":559200,"text":"Activism is the currency."},{"time":562079,"text":"I had no interest in citizenship\npurely as some sort of feel-good thing."},{"time":566503,"text":"For me, citizenship means you have to act,\nand that's what we required."},{"time":570804,"text":"And amazingly, it worked."},{"time":572789,"text":"Last year, more than 155,000 citizens\nin the New York area alone"},{"time":577520,"text":"earned enough points to qualify."},{"time":579447,"text":"Globally, we've now signed up citizens\nin over 150 countries around the world."},{"time":583835,"text":"And last year, we signed up\nmore than 100,000 new members"},{"time":587271,"text":"each and every week of the whole year."}]},{"cues":[{"time":589708,"text":"See, we don't need to create\nglobal citizens from nothing."},{"time":593835,"text":"We're already everywhere."},{"time":595788,"text":"We just need to be organized"},{"time":597991,"text":"and motivated to start acting."},{"time":600229,"text":"And this is where I believe\nwe can learn a lot from Davinia,"},{"time":603348,"text":"who started taking action\nas a global citizen back in 2012."},{"time":607925,"text":"Here's what she did."},{"time":609587,"text":"It wasn't rocket science."},{"time":611537,"text":"She started writing letters,"},{"time":613837,"text":"emailing politicians' offices."},{"time":616147,"text":"She volunteered her time\nin her local community."},{"time":619166,"text":"That's when she got active on social media"},{"time":621802,"text":"and started to collect pennies --"},{"time":624056,"text":"a lot of pennies."}]},{"cues":[{"time":626264,"text":"Now, maybe that doesn't sound\nlike a lot to you."},{"time":630252,"text":"How will that achieve anything?"},{"time":632502,"text":"Well, it achieved a lot\nbecause she wasn't alone."},{"time":636220,"text":"Her actions, alongside 142,000\nother global citizens',"},{"time":640674,"text":"led the US government\nto double their investment"},{"time":643339,"text":"into Global Partnership for Education."},{"time":645194,"text":"And here's Dr. Raj Shah,"},{"time":646757,"text":"the head of USAID,\nmaking that announcement."},{"time":649283,"text":"See, when thousands of global citizens\nfind inspiration from each other,"},{"time":653146,"text":"it's amazing to see\ntheir collective power."},{"time":655849,"text":"Global citizens like Davinia\nhelped persuade the World Bank"},{"time":659285,"text":"to boost their investment\ninto water and sanitation."},{"time":661984,"text":"Here's the Bank's president Jim Kim\nannouncing 15 billion dollars onstage"},{"time":666048,"text":"at Global Citizen,"},{"time":667334,"text":"and Prime Minister Modi of India\naffirmed his commitment"},{"time":670864,"text":"to put a toilet in every household\nand school across India by 2019."},{"time":676494,"text":"Global citizens encouraged\nby the late-night host Stephen Colbert"},{"time":680734,"text":"launched a Twitter invasion on Norway."},{"time":683710,"text":"Erna Solberg, the country's\nPrime Minister, got the message,"},{"time":686941,"text":"committing to double investment\ninto girls' education."},{"time":690440,"text":"Global citizens together with Rotarians\ncalled on the Canadian, UK,"},{"time":694259,"text":"and Australian governments"},{"time":695684,"text":"to boost their investment\ninto polio eradication."},{"time":698570,"text":"They got together and committed\n665 million dollars."}]},{"cues":[{"time":704309,"text":"But despite all of this momentum,"},{"time":707277,"text":"we face some huge challenges."},{"time":710008,"text":"See, you might be thinking to yourself,"},{"time":711912,"text":"how can we possibly persuade world leaders"},{"time":714260,"text":"to sustain a focus on global issues?"},{"time":717474,"text":"Indeed, the powerful American\npolitician Tip O'Neill once said,"},{"time":722581,"text":"\"All politics is local.\""},{"time":725762,"text":"That's what always\ngot politicians elected:"},{"time":728559,"text":"to seek, gain and hold onto power"},{"time":731605,"text":"through the pursuit of local\nor at very best national interests."}]},{"cues":[{"time":736185,"text":"I experienced this for the first time\nwhen I was 21 years old."},{"time":741113,"text":"I took a meeting"},{"time":742519,"text":"with a then-Australian Foreign Minister\nwho shall remain nameless --"}]},{"cues":[{"time":747655,"text":"[Alexander Downer]"}]},{"cues":[{"time":748970,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":751515,"text":"And behind closed doors,"},{"time":752761,"text":"I shared with him my passion\nto end extreme poverty."},{"time":755261,"text":"I said, \"Minister -- Australia\nhas this once-in-a-lifetime opportunity"},{"time":759204,"text":"to help achieve the Millennium\nDevelopment Goals."},{"time":761917,"text":"We can do this.\""},{"time":763806,"text":"And he paused,"},{"time":765268,"text":"looked down on me\nwith cold, dismissive eyes,"},{"time":768465,"text":"and he said, \"Hugh,"},{"time":769957,"text":"no one gives a funk about foreign aid.\""},{"time":772615,"text":"Except he didn't use the word \"funk.\""},{"time":775528,"text":"He went on."},{"time":776713,"text":"He said we need to look after\nour own backyard first."}]},{"cues":[{"time":779872,"text":"This is, I believe,"},{"time":781059,"text":"outdated, even dangerous thinking."},{"time":784059,"text":"Or as my late grandfather would say,"},{"time":785956,"text":"complete BS."},{"time":787958,"text":"Parochialism offers this false dichotomy"},{"time":790971,"text":"because it pits the poor in one country\nagainst the poor in another."},{"time":794501,"text":"It pretends we can isolate ourselves\nand our nations from one another."},{"time":798699,"text":"The whole world is our backyard,"},{"time":800790,"text":"and we ignore it at our peril."},{"time":802695,"text":"See, look what happened\nwhen we ignored Rwanda,"},{"time":804917,"text":"when we ignore Syria,"},{"time":806409,"text":"when we ignore climate change."},{"time":808336,"text":"Political leaders ought to give a \"funk\""},{"time":810543,"text":"because the impact of climate change\nand extreme poverty"},{"time":813230,"text":"comes right to our shore."}]},{"cues":[{"time":815110,"text":"Now, global citizens --\nthey understand this."},{"time":817744,"text":"We live in a time that favors\nthe global citizen,"},{"time":821018,"text":"in an age where every\nsingle voice can be heard."},{"time":823954,"text":"See, do you remember"},{"time":825146,"text":"when the Millennium Development Goals\nwere signed back in the year 2000?"},{"time":828636,"text":"The most we could do in those days\nwas fire off a letter"},{"time":831565,"text":"and wait for the next election."},{"time":833737,"text":"There was no social media."},{"time":835998,"text":"Today, billions of citizens\nhave more tools,"},{"time":839237,"text":"more access to information,"},{"time":841079,"text":"more capacity to influence\nthan ever before."},{"time":844151,"text":"Both the problems and the tools\nto solve them are right before us."},{"time":848377,"text":"The world has changed,"},{"time":850467,"text":"and those of us who look\nbeyond our borders"},{"time":852888,"text":"are on the right side of history."}]},{"cues":[{"time":856063,"text":"So where are we?"},{"time":857898,"text":"So we run this amazing festival,"},{"time":860289,"text":"we've scored some big policy wins,"},{"time":862628,"text":"and citizens are signing up\nall over the world."},{"time":865817,"text":"But have we achieved our mission?"},{"time":868651,"text":"No."},{"time":870285,"text":"We have such a long way to go."}]},{"cues":[{"time":872946,"text":"But this is the opportunity that I see."},{"time":876414,"text":"The concept of global citizenship,"},{"time":879716,"text":"self-evident in its logic but until now\nimpractical in many ways,"},{"time":885436,"text":"has coincided with this particular moment\nin which we are privileged to live."},{"time":890044,"text":"We, as global citizens,"},{"time":891220,"text":"now have a unique opportunity\nto accelerate large-scale positive change"},{"time":895831,"text":"around the world."},{"time":897554,"text":"So in the months and years ahead,"},{"time":899737,"text":"global citizens will hold\nworld leaders accountable"},{"time":902805,"text":"to ensure that the new Global Goals\nfor Sustainable Development"},{"time":905875,"text":"are tracked and implemented."},{"time":908048,"text":"Global citizens will partner\nwith the world's leading NGOs"},{"time":910950,"text":"to end diseases like polio and malaria."},{"time":914243,"text":"Global citizens will sign up\nin every corner of this globe,"},{"time":917434,"text":"increasing the frequency, quality"},{"time":920114,"text":"and impact of their actions."},{"time":922851,"text":"These dreams are within reach."},{"time":925503,"text":"Imagine an army of millions"},{"time":928067,"text":"growing into tens of millions,"},{"time":930288,"text":"connected, informed, engaged"},{"time":934638,"text":"and unwilling to take no for an answer."}]},{"cues":[{"time":938432,"text":"Over all these years,"},{"time":941230,"text":"I've tried to reconnect with Sonny Boy."},{"time":944770,"text":"Sadly, I've been unable to."},{"time":948611,"text":"We met long before social media,"},{"time":951479,"text":"and his address has now\nbeen relocated by the authorities,"},{"time":954267,"text":"as often happens with slums."},{"time":957923,"text":"I'd love to sit down with him,"},{"time":959381,"text":"wherever he is,"},{"time":961312,"text":"and share with him how much the time\nI spent on Smoky Mountain inspired me."},{"time":966680,"text":"Thanks to him and so many others,"},{"time":968453,"text":"I came to understand the importance\nof being part of a movement of people --"},{"time":972752,"text":"the kids willing to look up\nfrom their screens and out to the world,"},{"time":976743,"text":"the global citizens."},{"time":979104,"text":"Global citizens who stand together,"},{"time":981973,"text":"who ask the question \"Why?,\""},{"time":984663,"text":"who reject the naysayers,"},{"time":986938,"text":"and embrace the amazing possibilities\nof the world we share."}]},{"cues":[{"time":991240,"text":"I'm a global citizen."}]},{"cues":[{"time":993190,"text":"Are you?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":994841,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":996047,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}